{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"580e2c84-0272-4b6d-86e9-5b5dcb0443d7","content":"**MSTest.Sdk 4.x dropped the VSTest adapter entirely.** It only ships with **Microsoft.Testing.Platform** (the new runner). Since `vstest.console` relies on the legacy VSTest adapter to discover tests, it finds nothing.\n\n### Fix: replace `vstest.console` with `dotnet test`\n\n`dotnet test` in MSTest.Sdk 4.x uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform natively. In your CI pipeline, change:\n\n```diff\n- vstest.console.exe MyApp.Tests.dll\n+ dotnet test MyApp.Tests.csproj\n```\n\nIf you **must** keep `vstest.console` temporarily, you can re-enable the VSTest adapter by adding this to your `.csproj`:\n\n```xml\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>false</EnableMicrosoftTestingExtensionsCodeCoverage>\n  <TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>true</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nand setting `<EnableVSTestAdapter>true</EnableVSTestAdapter>` — but note this is a compatibility shim, not a long-term solution. Migrating to `dotnet test` is the recommended path.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"15621b10-e3b8-4764-8ed1-fe6f370a58b6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about the breaking change in MSTest.Sdk 4.x regarding VSTest compatibility. This is a well-known breaking change:\n\nStarting with MSTest.Sdk 3.8+, MSTest moved to Microsoft.Testing.Platform as the default runner. In MSTest.Sdk 4.x, support for the legacy VSTest runner was removed entirely. The `vstest.console` tool relies on the VSTest adapter (`Microsoft.VisualStudio.TestPlatform.TestFramework`), but MSTest.Sdk 4.x only ships with Microsoft.Testing.Platform support.\n\nKey points:\n- MSTest.Sdk 3.x defaulted to Microsoft.Testing.Platform but still included VSTest compatibility\n\n\n- MSTest.Sdk 4.x completely dropped the VSTest adapter, so `vstest.console.exe` can no longer discover or run tests from these projects\n- The solution is to switch to `dotnet test` which uses Microsoft.Testing.Platform, or run the test app directly with `dotnet exec`","outputTokens":580,"requestId":"5C20:C4D03:48EFAE:5BD489:69F56522"},"id":"e1c407c1-296b-4865-9502-c8e93486a941","timestamp":"2026-05-02T02:45:03.498Z","parentId":"cdc86f44-94bf-4607-9507-601d2210b0dd"}
